node.text:
On #InternationalWomensDay we’re celebrating women who work in conservation. 

This is Mondzongo Ruth Belvanie, the first female government ranger in Ntokou Pikounda National Park, Republic of Congo. Find out why this job is so important to her 💚🐘

Share if you think trailblazers like Ruth are an inspiration to women and girls everywhere! #IWD2021

#FemaleRanger #NtokouPikounda #ElephantConservation #WomenEmpowerWomen #IWD #ElephantsOfInstagram #Elephants #Conservation #NatureLovers #OurPlanetDaily #NaturePhotography #PlanetEarth

node.text:
Yesterday was #WorldWhaleDay 🐳

The Arctic is changing 🌡️💦🚢🔊 Arctic whales are facing unprecedented changes as human-made noise floods our oceans.

Tag your friends and family to raise awareness about the dangers of noise pollution. We need to tell governments around the world that we want #LessNoiseMoreLife to ensure a healthy ocean and a safe habitat for Arctic whales. 

📽️ Sound on 🔊

Shout-out to @linetestcollective for designing this stunning animation 🐋 

#Arctic #Whales #WhaleDay #ArcticWildlife #ArcticWhales #ArcticOcean #UnderWaterNoise

With the world’s eyes on the #Tokyo2020 #Olympics, we’re urging all to look at the future - a future where levels of air pollution keep rising. What might that world look like? 🤔

An estimated 9 out of 10 people breathe polluted air globally. 😰
And research suggests that exposure to air pollution could cause almost 9 million deaths each year.

❌🌲 If we continue to burn fossil fuels, use diesel and gasoline to power vehicles, clear forests and burn waste, air quality worldwide will only get worse. 

Creating a world where people and nature thrive is essential - DOUBLE TAP if you agree! And 👉 click the link in our bio to see more about the #Olympics of the future and learn how you can protect our shared home. #NoNatureNoSport #StrongerTogether

node.text:
Musa, a senior community ranger at Loita conservancy, bordering the Maasai Mara, sits with his son after a tiring day at work. 

Musa is responsible for overseeing one of the largest community and private sector owned conservation areas in the world, an important corridor in Kenya for the movement of elephants. 
His roles are vast — from mitigating human-wildlife conflict to ensuring his community has access to water. But so is his experience — he’s grown up alongside the people and wildlife he protects for the next generation. 

This #WorldRangerDay, we recognize rangers like Musa and reaffirm our commitment towards a safer and more inclusive environment for rangers to do their work safely, effectively and responsibly, for people and for nature. 

#conservation #WildlifeConservation #Kenya #elephants #MaasaiMara #Africa #AfricanSavanna

node.text:
Qui Shi is a member of China’s only all-women patrol team, monitoring the health of Dongning Forestry Bureau, one of the country’s last remaining habitats on the tiger range.

“Most of the team here are second or third generation forestry people. Our fathers and grandfathers walked these forests before us. As a child I couldn’t understand why my father was always away, always busy. Some of my teammates feel the same way, “ she says. 

Worldwide, women represent only 3-11% of the ranger profession. This #WorldRangerDay, we are reaffirming our commitment as members of the Universal Ranger Support Alliance to advocate for a safer and more inclusive environment for rangers of all backgrounds to do their work effectively and responsibly, for people and for nature. 

#conservation #WildlifeConservation #China #TigerConservation #Tigers #ProtectTigers

The #Tokyo2020 #Olympics are in full swing, with athletes from across the world competing for gold. But - with our planet in danger - what could the #Olympics of the future look like? 👇

Nature loss and the climate crisis not only devastate our home - the impacts will be felt (and are already being felt) by us, no matter where we are in the world. 

This means all areas of our lives, including sport, are at risk 😓 #NoNatureNoSport

So, what can we do? We may not all be world-class athletes, but we can all become champions for nature. And we can start today 🏆 

Tap the link in our bio to see what the future olympics could look like, and learn what we can do to avoid it! #StrongerTogether

🌳If we act today, we can secure a future with thriving rainforests.
